    12	//
    13	// openDatabase returns a `better-sqlite3` Database handle with the
    14	// project's standard pragmas:
    15	//
    16	//   journal_mode = WAL
    17	//     Concurrent reader / single writer; faster writes than the default
    18	//     `delete` mode. SQLite's WAL is a no-op on `:memory:` databases —
    19	//     SQLite refuses the change and the journal stays in `memory` mode.
    20	//     Test below documents both branches.
    21	//
    22	//   foreign_keys = ON
    23	//     Enforces FK constraints. SQLite's default is OFF for backwards
    24	//     compatibility with old apps; we always want ON so FK violations
    25	//     fail at write time, not silently corrupt the schema.
    26	//
    27	// Sync API: better-sqlite3 is fully synchronous. This matches D38's
    28	// SessionRouter sync write-through contract and D33's per-callback
    29	// atomic CAS expectations. No `await` needed for any DB op.
