 succeeded in 0ms:
     1	# CLAUDE.md：Codex IM Rich Client 项目规则
     2	
     3	## 项目目标
     4	
     5	本项目要实现一个基于 Codex App Server 的 IM rich client。Mac mini 上常驻运行 daemon，通过 Telegram、飞书、钉钉等 IM 控制 Codex App Server，保留 thread/turn/item、streaming、approval、diff、review、Computer Use 等能力。
     6	
     7	## 绝对不要做
     8	
     9	- 不要把项目实现成 OpenClaw 插件。
    10	- 不要通过解析 Codex CLI/TUI 终端输出实现功能。
    11	- 不要把 Vercel AI SDK 的普通 chat abstraction 作为 Codex 核心。
    12	- 不要公网暴露 Codex App Server。
    13	- 不要默认绕过 approvals。
    14	- 不要让 Computer Use 被普通 prompt 隐式触发。
    15	
    16	## 必须坚持的架构
    17	
    18	```text
    19	IM Adapter -> ChannelAdapter -> Core -> CodexRuntime -> AppServerClient -> codex app-server
    20	```
    21	
    22	核心层自研：
    23	
    24	- AppServerClient
    25	- CodexRuntime
    26	- EventNormalizer
    27	- ApprovalBroker
    28	- SessionRouter
    29	- SecurityPolicy
    30	- RenderScheduler
    31	
    32	IM 平台只通过 ChannelAdapter 接入。
    33	
    34	## 技术栈
    35	
    36	- TypeScript
    37	- Node.js 24+ (Node 20 reached EOL 2026-04-30; project bumped pre-Phase-1)
    38	- pnpm workspace
    39	- SQLite
    40	- Vitest
    41	- Telegram: grammY/native API
    42	- Feishu/Lark: @larksuiteoapi/node-sdk
    43	- DingTalk: dingtalk-stream-sdk-nodejs
    44	
    45	## 开发流程
    46	
    47	1. 先读 docs 中相关设计。
    48	2. 使用 Superpowers：brainstorming -> writing-plans -> TDD -> review -> finish。
    49	3. 使用 gstack：重要架构任务先 `/plan-eng-review`，高风险任务用 `/guard`，收尾用 `/document-release`。
    50	4. 每个任务只改计划内文件。
    51	5. 关键模块先写 failing tests。
    52	6. 每个 phase 结束调用 Codex CLI 做独立 review。
    53	
    54	## 常用命令
    55	
    56	```bash
    57	pnpm test
    58	pnpm typecheck
    59	pnpm lint
    60	pnpm protocol:generate
    61	pnpm smoke:app-server
    62	```
    63	
    64	## Codex CLI 的用途
    65	
    66	可以使用 Codex CLI 来：
    67	
    68	- 生成 App Server protocol types。
    69	- 运行 app-server smoke/debug。
    70	- 做独立 code review。
    71	- 生成测试计划。
    72	
    73	但运行时代码不能依赖“解析 Codex CLI/TUI 输出”。
    74	
    75	## 安全规则
    76	
    77	- 所有 approval 必须可审计。
    78	- 非白名单用户/群不能触发任务。
    79	- Computer Use 必须 `/cu` 显式触发。
    80	- deny app/deny command 不可被普通 approval 绕过。
    81	- 日志必须 redact secrets。
    82	
    83	## Method literal policy (Phase 1 tag-gate fix, 2026-05-01)
    84	
    85	Production source code must not scatter Codex App Server JSON-RPC method
    86	string literals. The boundary is enforced (partly by build-time grep
    87	guard, partly by code review) so that protocol-method drift is caught
    88	in one place when codex bumps versions.
    89	
    90	**ClientRequest method literals** (e.g. `"thread/start"`, `"turn/start"`,
    91	`"review/start"`):
    92	
    93	- Raw calls like `client.request("thread/start", ...)` are forbidden in
    94	  production `src` outside the approved central runtime method table.
    95	- The approved home: `packages/codex-runtime/src/runtime.ts` —
    96	  `REQUEST_METHODS` const declared `as const satisfies Record<string,
    97	  ClientRequest["method"]>`. Wrappers like `runtime.threadStart(...)` /
    98	  `runtime.turnStart(...)` are how downstream code invokes these methods.
    99	- CLI, daemon, and IM adapters MUST use `CodexRuntime` wrappers instead
   100	  of raw `client.request("...")`. If a wrapper is missing for a method
   101	  Phase N needs, add the wrapper to `runtime.ts` (with a `REQUEST_METHODS`
   102	  entry); do not duplicate the literal at the call site.
   103	
   104	**ServerRequest method literals** (e.g. `"item/fileChange/requestApproval"`,
   105	`"applyPatchApproval"`, `"account/chatgptAuthTokens/refresh"`):
   106	
   107	- Two approved homes (Phase 1 + Phase 2):
   108	  - `packages/core/src/approval-broker.ts` — `DispatchTable` typed
   109	    `as const satisfies Record<ServerRequest["method"], DispatcherSpec>`
   110	    plus the `_ExhaustiveDispatch` type-level guard.
   111	  - `packages/core/src/approval-request-kind.ts` (Phase 2 T2 / D18) —
   112	    `METHOD_TO_KIND` table used by `classifyApprovalRequest()`. This
   113	    is the SOLE place renderer / channel-core / wire-up code reaches
   114	    when classifying an approval; downstream code never reads the
   115	    raw method string.
   116	- T20 (Phase 2) replaced the Phase 1 `git grep -F` pipeline with a
   117	  filesystem walk over an explicit allowlist
   118	  (`packages/core/test/no-method-literals.test.ts` `SCANNED_DIRS` +
   119	  `ALLOWED_FILES`). Scope extended to `packages/render/src/**`,
   120	  `packages/channel-core/src/**`, plus `packages/im-*/src/**` (when
   121	  shipped). Plus an explicit T20.3 assertion that
   122	  `packages/core/src/decision-mapper.ts` contains zero method literals
   123	  (mapper switches on `ApprovalRequestKind`, never on raw strings).
   124	- Synthetic unknown-method tests must use names like `"future/unseen/
   125	  method"` and must not pretend to be real approval protocol methods.
   126	
   127	**Allowed exceptions** (legitimate references; not boundary violations):
   128	
   129	- `docs/**` — handoffs, plans, review reports, protocol audits.
   130	- `TODOS.md` — backlog tracking that may quote method names verbatim.
   131	- `packages/testkit/fixtures/**` and fixture metadata (`metadata.json`).
   132	- `scripts/**` — audit / verification scripts that read protocol evidence
   133	  (e.g. `scripts/verify-phase1-fixtures.mts`).
   134	- `**/README.md` examples that quote method names AS examples (CLI
   135	  README's "what `runtime send` exercises" section).
   136	- `packages/codex-protocol/src/generated/**` — ts-rs generated types
   137	  carry literals as discriminator strings; this is correct.
   138	- Test files (`**/test/**`) — tests may reference method names to
   139	  assert dispatch correctness; the grep guard exempts test paths.
   140	
   141	**Disallowed**:
   142	
   143	- `packages/cli/src/**` — raw `client.request("thread/start", ...)` etc.
   144	  Use `CodexRuntime` wrappers.
   145	- `packages/daemon/src/**` — same.
   146	- `packages/render/src/**` (Phase 2 +) — renderer switches on
   147	  `ApprovalRequestKind` from `classifyApprovalRequest()`, never on
   148	  raw method strings. F1 boundary.
   149	- `packages/channel-core/src/**` (Phase 2 +) — channel adapters
   150	  consume `ApprovalAction` (= `ApprovalUiAction`) only; the wire
   151	  shape is the broker's concern.
   152	- Future `packages/im-*/src/**` (Phase 3+) — same.
   153	- `packages/codex-runtime/src/**` — except inside the `REQUEST_METHODS`
   154	  const table itself.
   155	- `packages/core/src/**` — except inside `approval-broker.ts`'s
   156	  `DispatchTable` keys AND `approval-request-kind.ts`'s `METHOD_TO_KIND`
   157	  table. `decision-mapper.ts` MUST switch on `ApprovalRequestKind`
   158	  (T20.3 explicit assertion).
   159	
   160	If a future audit script needs to reference a method literal in
   161	production source code, document it in this section before adding.
   162	
   163	## Phase 2 redlines (carry forward to Phase 3+)
   164	
   165	In addition to the project-wide redlines (start of this file):
   166	
   167	- ❌ **No first-actor-wins** — `bindActorPolicy` is the only way to grant
   168	  approval permission. `resolve()` validates per-card per call.
   169	  See `packages/core/src/approval-broker.ts` `actorAllowed` /
   170	  `targetEqual`. (D19 / Codex round-1 P0-5)
   171	- ❌ **No `expirePending()` as a security boundary** — `expirePending`
   172	  is a sweep utility for audit/metrics. `resolve()` MUST also
   173	  lazy-check `Date.now() >= expiresAt` before settle (D20 / Codex
   174	  missing #4 / T11.3).
   175	- ❌ **No `entry.settleOnce` modification** — body byte-for-byte
   176	  locked at Phase 1 tag. All settle paths route through
   177	  `#settleEntry` (D21). Byte-identical guard test exists in
   178	  `packages/core/test/approval-broker-t7-public-surface.test.ts`.
   179	- ❌ **No `"approve"` wire decision** — v2 = `"accept"`; legacy =
   180	  `"approved"`. Mapper switches per `ApprovalRequestKind` (D11 /
   181	  Codex round-1 P1-1). `packages/core/src/decision-mapper.ts`.
   182	- ❌ **Production = `Supervisor`; `runtime-send` = dev/operator only**
   183	  (Codex Q6 / D16 / T22). `Supervisor.#spawnFresh` head asserts
   184	  `broker.isAttached()` with a load-bearing error message naming the
   185	  split. Daemon production wire-up MUST attach the broker before
   186	  passing it to Supervisor.
   187	- ❌ **F13 channel-core boundary** — `packages/channel-core/src/**`
   188	  has NO runtime import of `@codex-im/core`, `@codex-im/codex-runtime`,
   189	  or `@codex-im/app-server-client`. Type-only consumption via
   190	  `@codex-im/render` is allowed. Boundary tests
   191	  `packages/channel-core/test/no-broker-import.test.ts` +
   192	  `no-protocol-import.test.ts` enforce.
   193	- ❌ **C-P1 unknown-snapshot must render decline-only** — if a
   194	  `PendingApprovalSnapshot` reaches the renderer with
   195	  `classifyApprovalRequest(method) === "unknown"`, project to a
   196	  decline-only `ApprovalCard` with `target.riskLevel = "critical"`,
   197	  `actions = [{kind: "decline"}]`. Broker's `#handle` already
   198	  fail-closes at `-32601`; this is defense-in-depth at the renderer.
   199	
   200	## 结束任务前检查
   201	
