  1961	  per D42: `#enqueue(...)` for each event → `#drain()` → `endOfStream()`.
  1962	  Tests:
  1963	  (a) synthetics arrive in FIFO order with pre-buffered events;
  1964	  (b) `{done:true}` follows last synthetic;
  1965	  (c) idempotent on second call;
  1966	  (d) follow-up bare `endOfStream()` is a no-op;
  1967	  (e) **★ v2.4 P1-2 ★** waiter-already-blocked: spawn a consumer
  1968	      awaiting `.next()` BEFORE calling `endWithSynthetic`; assert
  1969	      the consumer receives the synthetic events one-by-one via
  1970	      the parked-waiter resolution path, then `{done:true}`.
  1971	      Without `#drain()` between `#enqueue` and `endOfStream`, this
  1972	      consumer would hang forever — the test proves the drain
  1973	      step is load-bearing.
  1974	  (f) optional: backpressure soft cap still applies to synthetics
  1975	      (exists test from earlier; demoted from required to optional
  1976	      since it's covered indirectly by `#enqueue` reuse).
  1977	  Sequenced before T19d.
  1978	- **T2a** — `database.ts` `openDatabase(path)` returns `Database` with
  1979	  WAL pragma + foreign-keys ON. One failing test verifies the pragmas.
  1980	- **T2b** — Migration runner: `runMigrations(db, dir)` walks the
  1981	  migrations directory + applies + records in `schema_version` table.
  1982	  One test for first-run apply.
  1983	- **T2c** — Migration runner idempotency: re-running applies nothing,
  1984	  asserts no SQL execution. One test.
  1985	- **T3a** — Migration 001 `schema_version` (records each migration
  1986	  applied); test that runner records the new row.
  1987	- **T4a** — Migration 002 `thread_bindings`; `BindingRepository.upsert`.
  1988	  Single test: upsert + findByTarget round-trip.
  1989	- **T4b** — `BindingRepository.list` + `delete`. Two tests.
  1990	- **T4c** — `BindingRepository` durable-write semantics (D38): insert
  1991	  fails if SQLite write fails; in-memory doesn't get optimistically
  1992	  populated. Test simulates write failure via read-only mount or
  1993	  filesystem error.
  1994	- **T5a** — Migration 003 `approvals`; `ApprovalRepository.upsert` +
  1995	  read. Test.
  1996	- **T5b** — `ApprovalRepository` redact roundtrip. Test inserts
  1997	  approval with bad-payload, asserts read returns redacted.
  1998	- **T6a** — Migration 004 `audit_log`; `AuditRepository.insert` +
  1999	  read. Test.
  2000	- **T6b** — `AuditRepository` redact roundtrip. Test.
  2001	- **T6c** — `AuditRepository` rate-limited failure (D31): inject a
  2002	  failing INSERT; assert single `audit.sqlite_unavailable` ring entry,
  2003	  subsequent failures aggregate to a counter. Test.
  2004	- **T6d** — Migration 007 `callback_tokens` (D34); `CallbackTokenRepository`:
  2005	  `insert`, `findByHash`, `casUpdate(hash, fromStatus, toStatus, fields)`,
  2006	  `pruneExpired`. Tests.
  2007	- **T6e** — `CallbackTokenRepository` hash-only storage assertion: raw
  2008	  token MUST NOT appear in any SQLite column. Test inserts via the
  2009	  helper, queries the underlying table, asserts no plaintext token
  2010	  bytes match.

